review_blob: Available only on draft around eastern and southern Idaho, the folks at the home pub had to start pouring it into wine glasses because pint drinkers were walking into the walls. It has a deceptive alcohol content of around 8 percent, which sneaks up on you. The appearance and aroma are heavy on the caramel, with a small head that leaves a little lace. Heavy alcohol content doesnt come through in the palate. A nice beer to sip over a long chat.
Beautiful amber-orange appearance; fits any season and just about any food.
